Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:05.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hello, it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:05.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你好 我是Scott Manley
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.21,0:00:10.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've talked about the rocket science of {\i1}the Expanse{\i0} in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.21,0:00:11.21,1080P-sgsm-50,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur4\move(-20,270,10,270,0,500)}这期视频详见youtu.be/JWZqp0QoXcw
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.21,0:00:10.11,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我在过去的节目中曾谈到过{\i1}苍穹浩瀚{\i0} 中的火箭科学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.48,0:00:14.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In that show, the fusion drives are a rare thing for science fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.48,0:00:14.00,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那个节目中 核聚变发动机是科幻小说中罕见的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.08,0:00:17.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}in that they are actually sort of within the laws of physics
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.08,0:00:17.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它们实际上是符合物理学规律
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.13,0:00:22.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}albeit likely beyond any technology that could be developed soon or possibly ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.13,0:00:22.53,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管很可能这技术开发不出来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.88,0:00:27.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In the TV show the spacecraft have engines that are able to provide powerful thrust
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.88,0:00:27.51,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在电视剧中 航天器的发动机能够提供强大的推力
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:32.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}comparable to the chemical rockets that we use and to launch rockets into space
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:32.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可与我们使用的化学火箭相媲美 并将火箭发射到太空
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.86,0:00:36.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but they're able to operate for days or even weeks at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.86,0:00:36.81,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它们能够一次运行几天甚至几周的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:43.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}like the ultra high efficiency ion propulsion systems used on deep space probes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:43.19,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就像今天深空探测器上使用的超高效离子推进系统
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.48,0:00:46.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It would be really nice
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.48,0:00:46.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将是非常好的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:52.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if there were something that we could imagine in real life that could do both, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:52.84,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果在现实生活中有什么我们可以想象的东西 能同时做到这两点的话 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.28,0:00:57.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And there are smart people that have come up with a few ideas over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.28,0:00:57.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这些年来 有些聪明的人已经想出了一些主意
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.86,0:01:04.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so I want to talk about one particular thing known as the nuclear saltwater rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.86,0:01:04.06,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我想谈谈一个特别的东西 被称为核盐水火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:06.96,1080P-sgbd-48,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's the brainchild of Robert Zubrin
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:06.96,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1000)}是罗伯特·祖布林的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.96,0:01:07.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you might have heard of him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.96,0:01:07.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可能听说过他
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:12.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because he is a sort of guy behind the Mars direct concept
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:12.30,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为他是火星直达概念的幕后推手
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.32,0:01:18.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which has sort of become the basis for most of the plans to send humans to the red planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.32,0:01:18.60,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这也算是启发了大多数将人类送入红色星球的计划
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:20.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So rocket engines
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:20.98,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么火箭发动机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.01,0:01:26.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they obviously work by sending out exhaust, reaction mass at high velocities in one direction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.01,0:01:26.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}显然工作原理是 在某个方向把化学反应产生的废气质量以高速排出
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.58,0:01:30.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the conservation of momentum means that you get thrust in the opposite direction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.58,0:01:30.61,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而动量守恒意味着你会被推向相反的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:34.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they need a lot of energy to throw out the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:34.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而发动机就需要大量的能量来抛出材料
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:39.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And conventional chemical engines the combustion of the fuel provides the bulk of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:39.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在传统的化学发动机中 燃料的燃烧提供了大部分的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:46.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}whereas in ion thrusters that energy comes from solar panels that are soaking up the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:46.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在离子推进器中 能量来自于吸收太阳能的太阳能板
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.20,0:01:53.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the power from those solar panels is actually pretty wimpy compared to the fury of the chemical reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.20,0:01:53.33,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以比起化学反应的狂暴 那些太阳能板的能量其实是很微弱的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.65,0:01:59.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but both of them are much lower energy density than what's available from nuclear reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.65,0:01:59.85,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它们的能量密度都比核反应的能量密度低得多
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.33,0:02:03.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now there are actually nuclear thermal engines
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.33,0:02:03.52,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么其实是有核热发动机的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:06.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that's where you have a nuclear reactor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:06.15,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是发动机里有核反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.15,0:02:09.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you blow propellant over it to cool it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.15,0:02:09.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后把推进剂吹到反应堆上使之冷却
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.33,0:02:13.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And so you can heat the propellant to a relatively high temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.33,0:02:13.34,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以你可以把推进剂加热到一个相对较高的温度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.54,0:02:17.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and use the reactor sort of continuously with a lot of propellant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.54,0:02:17.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并基本上不断地用推进剂冷却反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:23.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this may sound crazy but they've actually built and tested these in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:23.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 这可能听起来很疯狂 但实际上在过去 已经有人建造和测试这些发动机了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:27.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}in fact they did a lot of testing in a place known as Jackass Flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:27.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 他们在Jackass Flats做了很多测试
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.34,0:02:30.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The program to develop these was shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.34,0:02:30.85,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}开发这些的计划被终止了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:36.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Probably because it was a key step to potentially extending the Apollo program to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:36.40,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能是因为它是将阿波罗计划延伸到火星的关键一步
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.52,0:02:40.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and government really wasn't wanting to fund something as extravagant as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.52,0:02:40.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而政府也确实不想资助这么奢侈的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:44.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So anyway in your nuclear thermal thrusters
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:44.19,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以无论如何 对于你的核热推进器
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.44,0:02:47.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they're about twice as efficient as the best chemical engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.44,0:02:47.78,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们的效率大约是最好的化学发动机的两倍
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.15,0:02:51.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But there are limits on this because to make things better
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.15,0:02:51.14,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这是有限度的 因为要让效率变得更高的话
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.41,0:02:53.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the reactor needs to be hotter and hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.41,0:02:53.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}反应堆需要更热
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.08,0:02:56.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if it gets too hot then it'll melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.08,0:02:56.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 如果它变得太热 那么它就会融化
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.64,0:02:58.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean it won't melt down because it's in zero-G
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.64,0:02:58.87,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是指 它不会向下融化 因为在零重力的情况下不会向下
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:04.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it having a liquid or even vaporized core is not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:04.23,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但核心因此液化或者气化是不好的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:06.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean it sounds catastrophic, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:06.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是指 这听起来是灾难性的 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:11.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But there are actually ideas for gas core nuclear reactors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:11.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但实际上 有气芯核反应堆的计划
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:18.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where the reactor is actually a superheated plasma containing fissile uranium or plutonium.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:18.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}反应堆实际上是一个过热的等离子体 含有可裂变铀或钚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:22.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is obviously a technical challenge but that's a whole other video.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:22.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这显然是一个技术上的挑战 但把这些放到另一个视频去讲吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:25.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}No the nuclear salt water rocket works
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:25.81,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与之不同的是 核盐水火箭的工作原理
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:31.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}by having a sustained nuclear reaction in the propellant as it flows through the engine itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:31.69,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是推进剂在流经发动机本身时 持续发生的核反应
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:37.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's just like a chemical rocket which has a chemical reaction as the fuel flows through it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:37.90,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就像化学火箭一样 当燃料流过火箭时 火箭会发生化学反应
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.02,0:03:40.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but with it vastly more energy available to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.02,0:03:40.85,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但其可利用的能量却大大增加
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.13,0:03:44.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The exhaust from a chemical rocket is thousands of degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.13,0:03:44.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}化学火箭的废气是几千度的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:50.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it could be hundreds of thousands of degrees in a nuclear salt water rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:50.76,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在核盐水火箭中可能是几十万度
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.66,0:03:57.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the propellant is water with a uranium or plutonium salt dissolved in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.66,0:03:57.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以推进剂是溶解了铀或钚盐的水
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.81,0:04:03.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The original proposal had a two percent uranium tetrabromide mixture with regular water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.81,0:04:03.10,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最初的方案中是2%的四溴化铀与普通水的混合物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:08.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The uranium itself would also be enriched to about 20 percent uranium-235.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:08.46,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}铀本身也会被浓缩到大约20%的铀235
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:10.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's reactor grade uranium.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:10.43,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是反应堆级的铀
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.34,0:04:16.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So in that mixture it contains everything it needs to sustain a chain reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.34,0:04:16.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 在该混合物中 (这样的浓度)可以维持一个链式反应
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:18.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you get enough of it in the right place,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:18.29,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果在正确的地方得到足够多的铀
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:23.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you will have a critical mass and the neutron driven reaction will run away exponentially
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:23.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就会达到临界质量 而中子驱动的反应将以指数级别运行
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:26.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the water will explode into hot plasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:26.42,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而水会爆炸成热等离子体
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.85,0:04:32.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the first problem is making a fuel tank that can store huge quantities of propellant
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.85,0:04:32.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 第一个问题是制造一个可以储存大量推进剂的燃料箱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:37.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you do this by having a lot of neutron absorbing materials spread throughout the interior of the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:37.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这样的话就要把大量的中子吸收材料 铺满整个储罐的内部
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:41.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Things like boron which will soak up those excess neutrons
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:41.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}像硼这样的材料可以吸收多余的中子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:45.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}before they can drive a runaway reaction and ruin your day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:45.69,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以免反应失控 并发生意外
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:51.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you have a fuel leak by the way then you'd better hope that it doesn't accumulate in any one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:51.49,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}顺便说一下 如果燃料发生了泄漏 那么你最好希望它别积聚在任何一个地方
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.83,0:04:55.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Otherwise it will eventually react when it collects a critical mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.83,0:04:55.98,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}否则当它聚集到一个临界质量时 最终就会发生反应
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:05:00.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the neutron suppression is a key part of the fuel handling
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:05:00.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么中子抑制是燃料处理的一个关键部分
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:05.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that has to be maintained right up to the point where you actually want it to react.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:05.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这必须要恰到好处 该反应的时候就要反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:12.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So in simple terms you pump the salt water down boron lined pipes into the chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:12.78,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么简单来说 你把盐水从衬有硼的管子里抽到燃烧室去
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.01,0:05:15.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and if you do it at the right speed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.01,0:05:15.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果速度没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:19.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can get a highly energetic self-sustaining nuclear reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:19.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你就可以得到一个高能量的自我维持的核反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which generates incredibly energetic plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它能产生令人难以置信的高能等离子体
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:25.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's this plasma which generates the thrust.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:25.74,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而正是这种等离子体产生了推力
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:30.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This isn't like the slow chain reaction you get in a regular nuclear reactor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:30.32,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这不像普通核反应堆中的缓慢的连锁反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:33.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where it's only barely critical so they can control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:33.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那种反应中 它只是勉强超过临界状态 这样就可以得到控制
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.60,0:05:34.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is a reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.60,0:05:34.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这种反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.80,0:05:41.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where the criticality is maximized to burn as much fuel as possible before it expands into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.80,0:05:41.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其中临界状态是在扩散到太空中之前 最大限度地燃烧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.08,0:05:44.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's kind of like trying to replicate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.08,0:05:44.40,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这有点像是试图复制
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:49.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the prompt criticality conditions in the excursion that destroyed the chernobyl reactor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:49.78,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}摧毁切尔诺贝利反应堆事故的瞬发临界条件
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:53.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but then you keep it running at that level continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:53.52,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但你要让它持续在这个水平上运行
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.89,0:05:55.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Sounds fun doesn't it, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.89,0:05:55.60,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}听起来很有趣 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah the water is of course key to this whole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 当然 水是整个过程的关键
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:06:03.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Uranium at 20 enrichment doesn't undergo a chain reaction on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:06:03.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}铀在20%的浓度下不会发生链式反应
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:07.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because the highly energetic neutrons that come out of those fission events
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:07.62,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为这些裂变事件中产生的高能中子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:11.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}have a very low probability of triggering another fission event.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:11.89,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}触发另一次裂变事件的概率非常低
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.48,0:06:17.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but slower neutrons are much more likely to make further fissions possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.48,0:06:17.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但速度较慢的中子则更有可能促使进一步的裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:20.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the water basically acts as a moderator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:20.66,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么水基本上是起到了调节作用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:22.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Those highly energetic neutrons,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:22.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那些高能中子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.54,0:06:25.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they freshly liberated from a fission event,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.54,0:06:25.67,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}刚从裂变事件中释放出来
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:27.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}bounce around off the water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:27.87,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在水分子之间来回反弹
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:30.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}until they're moving around slowly enough
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:30.71,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}直到它们移动得足够慢
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:34.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that they can make more reactions happen and sustain your reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:34.59,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以至于可以让更多的反应发生 并使反应得以维持
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:41.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this bouncing around leads to another trick that's in play in the design.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:41.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这种反弹会在设计中起作用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:45.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So you want to keep this highly energetic reaction under control
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:45.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 你要让这种高能的反应处于控制之下
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.95,0:06:48.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because of course the neutrons are bouncing around in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.95,0:06:48.61,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为中子当然会在水里跳来跳去
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They actually get dragged along by the water flow, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.87,0:06:51.99,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上会被水流拖着走 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.02,0:06:55.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're bouncing off the water molecules and that takes time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.02,0:06:55.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从水分子上反弹是要花时间的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.07,0:06:56.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and so they end up getting pushed along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.07,0:06:56.70,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以它们最终会被推着走
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:59.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if the water flow is fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:59.71,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以如果水流够快
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:04.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can actually stop the neutrons running upstream into the rest of your engine
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:04.72,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上 你可以阻止中子向上游跑到发动机的其余部分
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:06.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is probably a good thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:06.00,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这基本是件好事
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:09.93,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because you don't want a nuclear reaction running up inside your engine plumbing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:09.93,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为你不希望核反应在你的发动机管道内发生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:12.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where you don't want nuclear reactions to occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:12.99,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是你不希望发生核反应的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.52,0:07:16.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Depending upon how you do the math
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.52,0:07:16.37,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}取决于你的计算方式
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:21.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you need to get the water moving maybe at around 66 meters per second
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:21.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你需要让水以66m/s左右的速度流动起来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:23.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it could be higher depending upon how you do your math.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:23.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能会更高 这取决于你如何计算
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:26.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But this is something that's sort of doable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:26.00,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这是具备可行性的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:29.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's not like supersonic water flows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:29.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并不像超音速的水流那样
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:35.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Of course that's about 240 kilometers per hour for those that are keeping track.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:35.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然了 对于那些还在认真看视频的 我解释一下 这大概是240km/h的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.28,0:07:42.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But yeah do that and the majority of the reaction will stay happening in the place where you want it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.28,0:07:42.61,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 是的 这样做 大部分的反应会停留在你想要的地方发生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:45.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So there's another way to think about this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:45.18,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以有另一种方式来思考这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.26,0:07:50.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that is as a continuous thrust version of the orion nuclear pulse drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.26,0:07:50.35,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是作为一个连续推力版的猎户座核脉冲发动机
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:55.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's where you take nuclear bombs and you set them off close to a pusher plate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:55.21,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就是把核弹放在靠近推板的地方引爆
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:56.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that pushes the spaceship along.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:56.82,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后推动飞船前进
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:08:01.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But instead you've got a continuous nuclear explosion happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:08:01.22,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但与之相反 这样做 核爆炸已经是连续发生的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:08.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So to generate thrust effectively you need to direct all this fire and fury.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:08.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以为了有效地产生推力 你需要引导所有狂暴的火焰
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:13.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}All these exploding gases need to be directed using a nozzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:13.21,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些爆炸的气体需要用喷嘴来引导
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:16.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But with the amount of heat and radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:16.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但由于热量和辐射量太大
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:21.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}any unprotected physical nozzle would vaporize in short order.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:21.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任何没有保护的物理喷嘴都会在短时间内汽化
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:26.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the design has a layer of regular clean water running around the outside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:26.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以设计中在外面有一层常规的清水流过
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.16,0:08:29.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that acts as an insulating layer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.16,0:08:29.59,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就像一个隔热层
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.72,0:08:32.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}protecting both the nozzle from the heat and the radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.72,0:08:32.96,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}保护喷嘴免受热量和辐射的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:34.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So some numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:34.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 列举一些数字
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:42.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The paper estimates that perhaps you'd only have 0.1 percent of the uranium 235 undergoing fission
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:42.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}论文估计 也许你只有0.1%的铀235在进行裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:46.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which at two percent concentration salt, 20 percent enrichment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:46.50,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2%浓度的盐溶液 20%的(铀235)浓度
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:50.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}gives you 3.4 gigajoules per kilogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:50.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样 能量密度可达3.4千兆焦耳每千克
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:54.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's about 900 times the energy density of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:54.71,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这大约是TNT能量密度的900倍
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:09:00.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that translates to an exhaust velocity of about 60 to 70 kilometers per second
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:09:00.62,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着排气速度约为60-70km/s
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:02.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}depending upon how good your nozzle is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:02.49,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}取决于你的喷嘴有多好
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.92,0:09:06.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's about the same as the exhaust velocity from ion thrusters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.92,0:09:06.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这和离子推进器的排气速度差不多
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:10.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but in this case you're no longer limited by the tiny amount of power
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:10.52,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在这种情况下 你不再受制于微不足道的功率了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:13.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that you can soak up through those solar panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:13.06,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是受限于太阳能板提供的功率
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:16.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the sample design that was in the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:16.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么论文中的样本设计
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:21.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It used an inlet pipe which was six centimeters in diameter like that size
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:21.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它使用了一个直径为6厘米的进水管 差不多就这种尺寸
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:25.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with a propellant flow of 200 kilograms per second through that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:25.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}通过管道的推进剂流量为200kg/s
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:29.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and this would generate a thrust of about 1300 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:29.40,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将产生约1300吨的推力
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.60,0:09:34.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That works out to a steady state power of 700 gigawatts
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.60,0:09:34.46,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这相当于700千兆瓦的稳态功率
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:38.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which by the way when chernobyl reached peak power during its explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:38.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}顺便说一句 当切尔诺贝利在爆炸时达到峰值功率时
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:41.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it was about 350 gigawatts for a fraction of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:41.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在一瞬间达到了约350千兆瓦
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.99,0:09:45.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is 700 gigawatts continuously right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.99,0:09:45.34,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这是持续的700千兆瓦 没错吧
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.38,0:09:47.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a non-stop chernobyl going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.38,0:09:47.46,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一个不停在发生的切尔诺贝利
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.31,0:09:53.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now that thrust is roughly equivalent to two F1 engines that they used on the Saturn V.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.31,0:09:53.51,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这个推力大约相当于土星五号上的两个F1发动机的推力
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:58.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Those of course to do that each required two and a half tons of propellant
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:58.66,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 每台F1发动机都需要两吨半的推进剂
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:04.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so if you only need 200 kilograms versus five tons that's about 25 times more efficient
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:04.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么如果你只需要200公斤 而不是5吨 那就是25倍的效率
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.01,0:10:06.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is a nice step up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.01,0:10:06.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一个不错的进步
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.68,0:10:14.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To be clear you really wouldn't want to use this as the first stage to a rocket on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.68,0:10:14.19,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要申明的是 你真的不想用它作为地面火箭的第一级
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.24,0:10:18.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it would spread nasty radioactive fission products all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.24,0:10:18.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它将把讨厌的放射性裂变产物扩散到所有地方
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:23.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It would make the Rocky Flats Plant nuclear facility cleanup look, well, easy in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:23.99,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这可比洛基平原工厂核设施的清理复杂多了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:27.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But in deep space that radioactive exhaust is going so fast
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:27.90,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在深空 放射性废气的速度是如此之快
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:32.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that it rapidly spreads throughout space and goes to almost zero concentrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:32.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}会迅速地扩散到整个空间 几乎达到零浓度
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.43,0:10:36.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}in fact some of it is going so fast it will leave the solar system all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.43,0:10:36.09,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 有些物质的速度非常快 甚至会一起离开太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.06,0:10:40.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now if you were to say look at SpaceX's Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.06,0:10:40.22,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 假设SpaceX的Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:43.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then build a version with a nuclear saltwater rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:43.25,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}换成了核盐水火箭的版本
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.25,0:10:45.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Same amount of propellant mass
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.25,0:10:45.15,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同样质量的推进剂
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:50.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Starship right now in theory gets about eight to nine kilometers per second of Delta V.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:50.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在的Starship理论上能获得8-9km/s的速度增量(dv)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:53.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You switch it up with a nuclear salt water rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:53.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果换成核盐水火箭的话
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.44,0:10:56.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You could get 150 kilometers per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.44,0:10:56.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}dv就能达到150km/s
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:10:59.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You could travel to Jupiter in a couple of months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:10:59.38,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}几个月后就可以到木星去了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:02.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And come back in a couple of months using single fuel load.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:02.98,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后几个月 同样的一罐燃料也可以用于返回
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.02,0:11:04.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's quite amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.02,0:11:04.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是相当惊人的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:10.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To people thinking about the future of space, futurists and science fiction writers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:10.72,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于思考未来太空的人 未来学家和科幻小说家来说
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.72,0:11:14.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the nuclear salt water rocket is actually pretty attractive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.72,0:11:14.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}核盐水火箭其实很有吸引力
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:18.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because there's nothing fundamentally about it that breaks the laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:18.17,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为从根本上来说 它并没有什么违反物理定律的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:21.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's no obvious showstoppers that a bright student can point out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:21.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至没有那种明显的问题 会被聪明的学生打断
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:27.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Sure the simplistic sketch in the paper would likely to have a lot more complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:27.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 论文中的简单草图很可能会更复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:28.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if it was turned into a real engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:28.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是在变成一个真正的发动机之后
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:33.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You'd probably need neutron sources and neutron absorbers near the injection point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:33.19,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在靠近推进剂注入位置的地方 你可能需要中子源和中子吸收装置
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:35.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You could reconfigure to control the reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:35.57,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你需要有能力重新配置以控制反应
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:39.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and while pumping fluids at this rate isn't too hard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:39.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然以这种速度泵送液体并不难
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:44.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there's a question of maybe how you would power those pumps without adding lots of excess mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:44.15,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但仍然存在一个问题 那就是在不增加大量多余质量的情况下为这些泵提供动力
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.18,0:11:47.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But these are easy problems that we can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.18,0:11:47.14,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这些都是我们能想到的简单问题
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:53.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Indeed it's entirely likely that there's fundamental parts of material science
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:53.22,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 这完全有可能是材料科学的基本部分
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.26,0:11:55.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that simply can't deliver the kind of properties
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.26,0:11:55.99,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是材料根本无法提供的那种性能
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.02,0:12:01.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that we would need to turn a theoretical possibility like this into an engineering reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.02,0:12:01.29,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这种性能正是我们所需要的 这样才能把这种理论上的可能性变成工程上的现实
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:04.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But just say it could be made to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:04.34,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但只是假设 这是能起作用的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:09.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then the same paper did the math for a more powerful more efficient version
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:09.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后同一篇论文为一个更强大更高效的版本做了计算
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:16.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}instead of using reactor grade uranium, it used weapons grade uranium, enriched in 90 percent uranium-235.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:16.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它没有使用反应堆级的铀 而是使用了武器级的铀 铀-235的浓度为90%
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:20.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then assumed more of the uranium undergoes fission
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:20.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后假设更多的铀进行裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.04,0:12:24.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and in that case something like this would have an exhaust velocity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.04,0:12:24.46,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这种情况下 像这样的东西会达到这种程度的排气速度
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:27.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}possibly over one percent of the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:27.45,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能超过光速的百分之一
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:34.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then you'd be in the position to send spacecraft to other stars in decades rather than centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:34.60,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后你就可以在几十年内而不是几百年内 把航天器送到其他恒星去了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.17,0:12:40.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So even if science delivers the ability to fly around the solar system in a few months
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.17,0:12:40.89,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以即使科学提供了在几个月内绕太阳系飞行的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:44.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}by riding a continuous nuclear explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:44.06,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}通过乘坐这种连续核爆炸作为动力的飞船
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.58,0:12:49.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we'll still be able to dream of a sci-fI future where the ships could go faster still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.58,0:12:49.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们仍然可以梦想一个飞船可以跑得更快的科幻的未来
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.18,0:12:52.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.18,0:12:52.82,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是Scott Manley 切记 注意飞行安全
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:13:12.30,1080P-sgbd-4s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:13:12.30,1080P-sgsm-6s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[音乐]
